<br>
A chest x-ray is around 50 mrem, the average yearly dose for an American is about 360 mrem. 50 rem stretched over several years will increase the risk of cancer later in life, but does not present an imediate health risk and could be further reduced by adding additional shielding. In some areas of the world yearly doses in the thousands of mrem can be found without a noticible increase in the cancer rate.<br>
<br>
Aluminum is one such material usualy considered for structural pieces, the isotopes produced when exposed to radiation produced by nuclear fission, or other types for that matter, have short half-lives (minutes to seconds), thus the total activity level will go down rapidly. The bomb material is largely projected in other directions (the blasts are mostly omni-directional) and that which does impact does not enter the craft and therefore is not an issue.<br>
<br>
You asked before how the craft would be propelled if most of the blast did not intercept the craft. The bomb is incased in a dense radiation case (nominaly out of natural uranium for opacity) with an open neck at one end. This channel is filled with an absorbative filler material (sometimes byrillium was considered) with a disk of dense propellant at the end (densities ranged from tungstun to water depending on design). When the bomb exploded the radiation case contained the energy long enough for the channel filler to absorb energy from the photons (mostly x-rays) coming from the reaction. The filler then ionizes and delivers a shock wave to the propellant, ionizing it and projecting it towards the pusher. It is this dense propellant that makes up the first wave of plasma followed by the filler. This material also absorbs much of the radiation coming off the core, reducing shielding requirements. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovin>Sovin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tachyon Wrangler</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/11/03 10:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/images/offedge.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Factoids</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
